<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="180" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d180">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-12-03"><hi rend="italic">December 3,
                                1897</hi></date>. (Received December 18.)</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 207.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reply to your instruction No. 227, of
                            November 20, containing a report upon the cases of trichinae in German
                            pork, based upon a careful investigation made by the Secretary of
                            Agriculture, I beg to say that the interesting and valuable data
                            contained therein will be transmitted immediately to the Imperial
                            foreign office.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">And. D. White.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>